Containeruniface_104vli1665702682321.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vli1665702682321.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vli1665702682321.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vli1665702682321\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Create a thread that listens for interprocess communication (IPC)\n    messages.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vli1665702682321__topic_d140741e1_d140742e1_d140743e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vli1665702682321__p_d140744e1_d140745e1_d140746e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$IPC_ASYNC</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vli1665702682321__section_ywv_45x_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d318886e59\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vli1665702682321__table_d16874e1_d16875e1_d16876e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">application assignment files </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vli1665702682321__section_odb_p5x_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d318886e105\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vli1665702682321__p_d140753e1_d140754e1_d140755e1\">This assignment setting causes a thread to be created\n        at application start-up that listens for IPC messages. For each received message, the\n        receiveMessage trigger (at application level or component level) is fired and the message is\n        returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ncx1686824523526.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$result</a><p>Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ghq1665702608876.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger receiveMessage</a><p>Reacts to asynchronous messages that come from outside the application.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533071\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533071\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$IPC_ASYNC Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 30, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Create a thread that listens for interprocess communication (IPC) messages. $IPC_ASYNC Defaults Assignment file: application assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description This assignment setting causes a thread to be created at application start-up that listens for IPC messages. For each received message, the receiveMessage trigger (at application level or component level) is fired and the message is returned in $result . Related Links $result Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events. trigger receiveMessage Reacts to asynchronous messages that come from outside the application. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}